comment.undefined: Session class describes a session of gameplay.
The Game class describes a game product that can be played by a player.
Curiosity describes funny random things that can happen or be found in the game.
Game_Event describes an event that takes place in a game without straight player interaction. GameEvents are often very specific for each game.
Feature describes an ability or characteristic. For example, a sword could have “damage dealing” ability and a bottle of water could be “potable”.

comment.en: Location defines the location in map where the players die the most.

comment.undefined: The difficulty achievement describes succeeding in a game on a difficulty level. An example could be completing the “Doom” game on Nightmare difficulty level.

comment.en: What are the best video games for users who uses virtual reality .It defines all the games that can run on HMDs (Head Mounted Displays) system.

comment.undefined: Collection type of achievement is typically rewarded from collecting an amount of certain items in a game.
Item portrays any item that exists in a game. The item can either be just visual part of the game or a concrete usable item.

comment.en: Person describes the entity playing the game. This can be either a human or a computer.
PlayerEvent describes a Event that is caused by the player.

comment.undefined: Minigame achievement describes success in mini-games that have been included in a certain game but are not vital for completing the game.
InAppPurchaseEvent describes an event that is related to making a purchase with real money inside a game. This is a subclass of InstantaneousEvent because it happens at certain moment in time.
Paragon is a rare achievement that is given only to limited number of players.

comment.en: Map defines the favriot map of the player.

comment.undefined: Event class describes an event that happens during the gameplay at a certain moment in time. This can be a player gaining an achievement, killing an enemy or making an in-app purchase.
Achievement is a reward gained in a game due to some event accomplished in the game. Achievements are commonly used in game industry to reward players for having accomplished tasks in the game.

comment.en: Completion type of achievement is usually rewarded from successfully completing a certain goal or subgoal in a game.

comment.undefined: SpecialPlayStyle achievement is awarded to players after playing a game in special fashion. Often this is something harder than the regular play and requires more player experience to excel in it.

comment.en: Video Games are classified by platforms where they can run and played by player.

comment.undefined: The GainEvent describes an event that is related to character/player gaining something in a game.
The EasyMode difficulty achievement describes succeeding in a game on a easy level

comment.en: GameProduct is anything that is for sale inside a game. These can be either normal game items purchased with in-game currency or with real world money.
LoseEvent describes an event that is related to character/player losing something in a game. This is a subclass of GameEvent as gaining something is related to a specific game.

comment.undefined: The Player describes the entity playing the game. This can be either a human or a computer. Player class is used to keep a profile of a certain playing entity and to connect all the games, achievements and characters he/she has. The Player is a subclass of Person as it contains all relative information of a certain person.

labels.en: thousand hours of world of tanks

comment.undefined: Veteran achievement is an award that is given for accumulating a lot of play hours or game actions.
Fandom achievement is related to doing some true fan activities.

comment.en: What are the best video games for linux based users.It defines all the games that can run on linux based operating system.

comment.undefined: Genre class describes the genre a game belongs to. All of the games have at least one genre. Examples of this are RPG, Simulator and Adventure
Multiplayer achievement describes anything that can be awarded to one or multiple players due to their gameplay in multiplayer.

comment.en: Gaming Companies are the companies that developed video games for users.

comment.undefined: Character is any actor that can exists in a game. A character  can be a human-like creature as seen traditionally in video games. However, a character could also be a car, a paddle in game of Pong or spaceship of a space shooter game.

comment.en: What are the best video games for android-based users.It defines all the games that can run on android operating system.

comment.undefined: The Intermediate Mode difficulty achievement describes succeeding in a game on a Intermediate level

comment.en: PlayingArea is the description of a place where the gameplay takes place. All of the games have some kind of area where they are played in.

comment.undefined: Loyalty achievement is used to give recognition to loyal players.
Virtuosity describes an achievement that is awarded for playing masterfully in the game.
Tutorial achievement is  awarded to a player for trying out various features of the game. This is often related to learning how to play the game, how the controls work and how the game logic works.

Leaderboard class describes a ranking system of the players. There can be multiple rankings in a game, for example, the kill-count ranking of Modern Warfare or the best time listing of Formula 1 game.

comment.undefined: Menu_Event describes an event that is related to interacting with the ingame menu.
Lucky describes an achievement that is awarded to the player in a lucky situation.
The HardMode difficulty achievement describes succeeding in a game on a hard level
